hile setting them in a sweeping synthesis of Mediterranean and Christian history. From the Empress Galla Placidia and Theoderic the Gothic king, who both experienced being taken as hostages, to the amazing cosmographer of Ravenna and the doctor who strengthened expert Greek medical knowledge in Italy, Herrin demolishes the idea that the West just descended into the medieval "Dark Ages."Beautifully illustrated and drawing on the latest archaeological findings, this monumental book provides a bold new interpretation of Ravenna's lasting influence on the culture of Europe and the West.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aArian Baptistry.  aByzantine architecture.  aChurch of San Vitale.  aCity of Mosaics.  aDeborah Mauskopf Deliyannis.  aEternal Ravenna.  aEurope's greatest cities.  aExarchate of Revenna.  aFrom the Etruscans to the Venetians.  aGalla Placidia Mausoleum.  aJustinian mosaic.  aJutta Dresken-Weiland.  aMariëtte Verhoeven.  aMassimiliano David.  aRavenna in Late Antiquity.  aThe Early Christian Monuments of Ravenna.  agreat cities of Europe.  amedieval history.  amosaics of Ravenna.  amosaics of San Vitale.  awhere in Italy should I visit?.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package 2019z978311066336508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2019z978311065204840uhttps://doi.or